<!--
=======================================================
ARRANGER NOTES — The Love of God, D major, 3/4, 25 mm.
=======================================================

VOICING PLAN:

Phrase 1 (mm. 1–8) — Introduction, light texture, building:
  m1  pickup:  LH D2-A2-D3 open 5th+octave (pattern "334"), RH D4-F#4 just a 3rd — sparse
  m2  I→IV→I:  LH D2-A2-D3 root pos "334", RH D4-A4 open 5ths, brief IV and I cadence
  m3  I:       LH arpeggio D3-A3 / F#3-D3 / A2-D3-A3 inner motion, RH single-note ascent D-F#-A
  m4  V→IV→V:  LH V A2-E3-A3 then passing G2-D3 (IV color), then V A2-C#3-E3 close
  m5  I→ii→I:  LH 4-note I D2-A2-D3-F#3 ("334+3"), then Em diatonic, return to I
  m6  I→IV→I:  LH 4-note I with F#3 top, brief IV G2-B2-D3, I cadential A2-D3-A3
  m7  V:       LH alternating V positions — A2-E3-A3 / E2-B2-E3 / A2-C#3-E3 — inner motion
  m8  V7→IV→I: LH 4-note V7 A2-E3-G3-C#4 (full seventh chord), IV G2-D3-G3, resolve I

Phrase 2 (mm. 9–12) — Upper octave, build:
  m9  I→ii→I:  LH 4-note I D2-A2-D3-F#3, Em diatonic 3-note, return I
  m10 IV:       LH IV7 4-note G2-D3-G3-B3, then G-chord variants
  m11 I→vi:    LH I→I¹→Bm motion, F#2 bass on beat 2 for I first inversion color
  m12 V→V7:    LH A2-E3-A3-C#4 then V7 full — tension before cadence

Phrase 3 (mm. 13–16) — Echo of Phrase 2, slightly richer:
  m13 IΔ→ii→I: RH adds C#5 (maj7 color) — emotional peak of inner phrases
  m14 IV:       RH reaches G5 on beat 2 — highest RH note in phrases 2-3
  m15 I→vi:    I¹ (F#2 bass) on beat 2 for inner color, fuller top
  m16 V→iii:   Deceptive cadence V→F#m — harmonic surprise, both hands rich

Phrase 4 (mm. 17–20) — Climax, fullest texture:
  m17 IΔ→ii→I: RH 4 notes (IΔ7), LH 4 notes — 8-voice saturation
  m18 IV→V→IV: Both hands 3-4 notes throughout, E5 in RH — upper peak
  m19 I→IV:    Both hands 3-4 notes, LH F#3 top note on I, B3 on IV
  m20 Vs4→V→V7: RH suspension D5 on beat 1 (Vsus4), resolves down; LH full V7 at end

Phrase 5 (mm. 21–25) — Final verse, broad then converge:
  m21 I→ii→I:  LH 4-note I again, broad and full
  m22 IV→V→IV: RH extends to G5 again; LH 4-note IV both times
  m23 I→I¹→vi: I first inversion (F#4 in RH on beat 2), Bm with F#5 in RH — high color
  m24 V→V7→iii: Full V7 (4-note LH A2-C#3-E3-G3), deceptive to F#m; RH three notes each beat
  m25 final:   Quiet convergence — RH D4-F#4-A4 triad, LH D2-A2-D3-F#3 root pos

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:

1. Contrary motion between hands throughout: LH bass moves down while RH moves up
   (most visible in m3, m7, m10).

2. Common-tone retention: F#3 in LH is held across I→I¹ changes in mm. 15, 23;
   A3 in LH carries across I→V in m4.

3. Inner line F#→G→A in LH tenor (m4 beat3→m5 beat1→m5 beat2): stepwise chromatic color
   beneath a static outer bass.

4. The descending C#5→B4 in the melody at m18/m22 is supported by the V (A4-C#5-E5) →
   IV (G4-B4-D5) in RH — parallel descent that frames the vocal line without doubling it.

5. Suspensions: m12 beat3 has V7 full in LH (A2-C#3-E3-G3), setting up phrase-end tension
   that resolves strongly to the I at m13. Similarly m20 beat1 Vsus4→V→V7 creates a
   three-beat dominant tension arc.

6. F#m (③m) at m16/m24 beat3: the bass drops to F#2, creating a deceptive cadence
   that avoids a premature tonic. The iii chord is approached by step from the V bass.

TEXTURE ARC:

mm. 1–4   (Phrase 1a): Sparse — 2-3 note RH, 3 note LH. D4-A4 range in RH.
mm. 5–8   (Phrase 1b): Building — 3 note RH, 3-4 note LH. Dominant tension in m8.
mm. 9–12  (Phrase 2):  Upper octave — RH reaches D5-G5 range; LH fills octave below.
mm. 13–16 (Phrase 3):  Echo with color — IΔ7 color, F#m deceptive cadence.
mm. 17–20 (Phrase 4):  Climax — 4 notes in both hands most beats. V7 prolonged.
mm. 21–25 (Phrase 5):  Final verse — broad at opening, then quiet convergence to I root.

The piece begins with open, hollow voicings (P5 + P8 in LH) and ends with the same
voicing, creating a frame. The climax at m17-18 is the broadest harmonic moment,
with 4-note chords in both hands and RH reaching E5-G5.
-->
